import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/about.css';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="About - Dmitry Gladkikh"
  description="Dmitry Gladkikh - a C++ / Python developer based in Novosibirsk. 3 years in computer vision and engineering software. How I got here and what I'm looking for."
>
  <article class="about">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        C++ / Python developer with 3 years of experience in computer vision, measurement
        software, and backend development. Based in Novosibirsk, open to remote, hybrid,
        and relocation.
      </p>

      <h2>How I got here</h2>
      <p>
        I started with C++ at university - simple console programs and basic algorithms.
        Then I took courses in Python and backend development (Django, DRF, PostgreSQL, Celery,
        Redis), took on freelance work along the way, and later joined Aviaspetstest, where
        I still work today.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over three years I went from early template-matching tasks to designing complete
        measurement systems - from low-level camera work in C++ to application logic, GUI,
        and REST API in Python.
      </p>

      <h2>What I enjoy</h2>
      <p>
        Work with real substance to it: image processing algorithms, working with industrial
        hardware, designing systems end to end - from the computational core to APIs and
        infrastructure. I'm drawn equally to computational computer vision and to backend
        work: both come with a real problem to solve, not boilerplate.
      </p>
      <p>
        When measurements from your code are used on a test bench and the result depends on
        them - that's the best feedback a developer can get.
      </p>

      <h2>My own infrastructure</h2>
      <p>
        Outside of work I run my own infrastructure: a home GitLab on a mini-PC, a private
        network over Tailscale with a self-hosted coordinator, CI/CD pipelines to production
        servers, automated backups. My personal projects run on it - a CRM for the family
        business built with Django, a utility Telegram bot, and various experiments.
      </p>

      <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
      <p>
        Long-term projects where I can shape product quality. Backend, computer vision,
        systems software - substantial work where the quality of the solution matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        Happy to talk - reach out on <a href="https://t.me/Midnight_Fruit">Telegram</a>
        or by <a href="mailto:dima.gladkikh.2016@mail.ru">email</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>